# .templatesyncignore — starting point for a FRESH child scaffold that wants MECHANICAL
# tooling sync from the template via AndreasAugustin/actions-template-sync.
#
# The mature FGDH child repos (pds-query-broker / cross-hub-patientportal /
# fttp-fhir-dispatcher) do NOT mechanically sync — they share only the skills/ toolkit and
# use the `template-updater` skill (+ the template-sync-check notifier) instead, because a
# whole-repo file sync from this doc-skeleton template would pull files that don't belong
# in a real project. Keep this file only if you enable actions-template-sync.
#
# Rule of thumb: sync TOOLING (skills/**, shared workflows), never CONTENT.

# Content & project-specific — the child owns these:
docs/arc42/*.md
docs/adr/**
README.md
AGENTS.md
CLAUDE.md
CHANGELOG.md
version.txt
.release-please-manifest.json
release-please-config.json
.arc42-template.json
LICENSE
LICENSE-docs.md

# Dated report snapshots (keep the convention doc):
docs/reports/*.md
!docs/reports/README.md

# Child-customized skills — add your own so a sync never clobbers them, e.g.:
# skills/security-reviewer/**
